

     
      This illustrates how to show visitors to a site which tab they are currently on. The article outlines how to create a script that manipulates the z-indices of graphical tabs to pull the one that is clicked to the top layer and show the content in that tab. There is a simple introduction to the div tag, the z-index property and DHTML scripting in general.  [Resource-Type: Article; Category: Java Script; XRating: 3]
     
    
